bug.short_desc: TestRunner: Not all UI controls are useable after adapting the size of the window

long_desc.thetext:
If the user does resize the browser window of the testrunner to a specific size some controls are not accessible anymore. The toolbar items are grouped together with the use of toolbar overflow handling, but these widgets are out of reach.
The attached screeshot shows the details.
Created attachment 944 TestRunner with adapted window size

Looks like a simple problem we sometimes have if the content has a min size which is bigger than the viewport. The Toolbar then, ofc stays the same size as the content. So I guess the problem is solved as soon as the content looses its min size.
@Daniel: Do you think we should fix that for the release?
The controls are still accessible at a screen width of 1024 pixels. Since we don't expect developers to use this tool on lower-res screens, we think this is acceptable.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
